# Web (reactive frontend)

- Stack: Vite + React + TypeScript + Tailwind; shadcn-style primitives under
  `web/src/components/ui/`.
- API calls go through the hand-written client in `web/src/api/`, kept in sync
  with `contracts/openapi.yaml`. Never hand-roll a `fetch` to a backend endpoint
  outside that client. Base URL: `VITE_API_BASE_URL` (default
  `http://localhost:8080`).
- Server/async UI state: local React state (`useState`) in the fetching component
  for now — no global store and no React Query until a second remote screen needs
  shared cache. Inject the API client via props when testing.
- Components: one component per file under `web/src/components/`; colocated
  `*.test.tsx` next to the component; shared UI primitives in
  `web/src/components/ui/`.
- New component with any logic (not pure presentational) → component test with
  Testing Library (Vitest). New user-facing product flow → Playwright e2e
  (deferred for the greeting harness; add when a real flow lands).
- Loading/error/empty states are required for every data-fetching component, not
  an afterthought — write them in the same pass as the happy path.
- Run `npm run lint` + `npm test` (and `npm run build` before PR) from `web/`
  before calling frontend work done.
